The paper deals with query processing against RDF data sets, which is a topic related to databases (cs.DB). The proposed approach involves both machine and human computation, which suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the quality of query results, which is a concern in information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the use of crowd computing raises issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CYBER).
